Key Match Events: Gabriel Dadzie scored Djibouti's first goal in the qualifiers through a penalty.
Mohamed Aden scored for Djibouti in the 25th minute.
Wondimu Dibaba scored for Ethiopia in the 31st minute.
Mouktar Youssouf scored for Djibouti in injury time (90+4').
Pre-Game Insights: Djibouti will be hoping to secure their first points in World Cup qualifying when they host Ethiopia.
Djibouti have lost all five of their previous meetings against Ethiopia.
Ethiopia are searching for their third ever World Cup qualifying victory.
Ethiopia have not scored in this qualifying campaign and are hoping to end their goal drought.
